<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="160" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,151,896]" pageId="9" pageNumber="160">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,318,583,608]" pageId="9" pageNumber="160">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body chocolate brown to red brown; head chocolate brown with small red brown spots, eyes dark brown to black, posterior margin contiguous with pronotal collar; first antennal segment brown, apically red, clublike and curved, second segment yellow, last segments dark; apical collar of pronotum brown, pronotal disk light brown basally, medially and apically dark red brown, posterior margin yellowish brown; mesoscutum covered; scutellum brown, except sub-apex red brown and apex yellow; legs yellowish brown to red, base of femora yellow, apex dark brown, tibial spines yellow; hemelytra brown, with darker areas, lateral margin of corium sometimes broadly infuscate, cuneus brown mottled with red-brown, membrane brown, veins red.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="160" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,151,896]" pageId="9" pageNumber="160">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,836,861]" pageId="9" pageNumber="160">Discussion.</emphasis>
In its external anatomy, the 
<typeStatus box="[710,758,837,861]" pageId="9" pageNumber="160">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[816,923,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Adelphocorisella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="relata">
<emphasis box="[816,923,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="160">A. relata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
conforms to our diagnosis of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[151,342,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Adelphocorisella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,342,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="160">Adelphocorisella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We therefore suggest the new combination.
</paragraph>
